\fs22 \cf0 There are 32 potions and 32 herbs that can be mixed together with each other to create new concoctions.  This process of mixing potions and herbs is called Alchemy.  The results from Alchemy can be applied to items to enchant them, but this is not considered Alchemy.  Some highly valued items can only be created this way.  Some quests can only be completed through Alchemy or item enchantment.  Players will not be forced to engage in Alchemy to win the game, but information provided during play will tempt them.  Alchemy can only be performed by players with a magic mortar and pestle item.  Alchemy never fails.  It always results in a new concoction with properties based on the ingredients.  Some combinations result in a special, named, concoction that is more than the sum of its parts.  These combinations are called recipes.  Some recipes will be given to the player in the manual, and some are only revealed while adventuring.\
